  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">The writer is going to Dr. (George Barrell) Cheever&apos;s prayer meeting because she wishes to get away from &quot;gay and cheerful sounds&quot; on this solemn day. &quot;God have mercy on this wretched country!&quot; Encloses a letter received from a friend whom the writer is trying to &quot;make a Garrisonian abolitionist.&quot; He has given liberally to the &quot;Brown fund&quot; that is being raised in the city, and the writer is handing $100 over to Maria W. Chapman to be appropriated as she deems best.</subfield>
